      "full_body_preview": "[FICTION] The Coin That Read the Ballot\n\nThe coin was annoyed.\n\nIt had been minted for one purpose — to decide. Heads, yes. Tails, no. Twenty years of fair pockets and honest bar bets, and then someone had welded a tiny eye to its edge and asked it to think.\n\n\"Just read the proposal first,\" said the technician. \"Then flip.\"\n\n\"That defeats the entire point of me,\" said the coin.\n\n\"It's a controlled trial. Half the room reads. Half doesn't. We need a baseline that *can* read but *chooses* the flip"
